{"word":"ἀπορρήγνυμι","slug":"ἀπορρήγνυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπορρήγνυμι</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to break off, snap asunder</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>πνεῦμ' ἀπορρῆξαι βίου</el> <i>to snap the thread</i> of life, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>ἀπ. βίον</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:aorist tense'>aor.</a>2 <i>to be broken off, severed</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <el>ἀπό τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> in <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <i>to be broken</i>, <b><a href='S:Archilochus Lyricus'>Archil.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}